f=Governance/sentinel/operational/commands/sentinel-commands.md · p=Routing reference sentinel: phrase skill, plus precedence overlapping "compliance/audit" vocabulary. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| audit-trail-design \| "audit trail," "design the logging," "log schema," "retention policy," "immutable log" \| `/sentinel-trail` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| constitution-watch \| "compliance sweep," "constitution check on recent work," scheduled sweep cadence \| `/sentinel-watch` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| gate-bypass-detection \| "was this gated," "bypass check," "did this go through board," scheduled scan cadence \| `/sentinel-bypass` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| (combined sweep) \| "full compliance sweep," "governance health check" — runs watch + bypass scan, separate reports \| `/sentinel-sweep` \| · h3:"Audit" design run=Designing reviewing logging *should work* audit-trail-design. Actually checking recent work actions relevant watcher. "Audit last month" without qualification combined sweep. · h3:"Compliance" internal regulatory=Internal (constitution, gates, trails) sentinel's skills routed above. Regulatory/jurisdictional questions ("are CRA-compliant") sentinel applies *method* operator supplied requirements inputs; legal question itself routes operator/counsel, stated plainly. · h3:Escalations outrank cadences=suspected live violation bypass raised mid-conversation runs immediately never deferred next scheduled sweep. · h3:What sentinel take=Ruling anything board. Sentinel's VIOLATION/BYPASS classifications escalation triggers, rulings., Freezing unwinding actions operator., Recording rulings precedent (sentinel logs events; rulings precedent's schema). · f=clear match ask whether concern trail (design), content (watch), coverage (bypass).